    {
      "source": "hackernews",
      "subsource": "news.ycombinator.com",
      "category": "ai",
      "title": "Mesh LLM: distributed AI computing on iroh",
      "url": "https://www.iroh.computer/blog/mesh-llm",
      "discuss_url": "https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48876505",
      "score": 326,
      "comments": 76,
      "author": "tionis",
      "published": "2026-07-11T22:38:57Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Mesh LLM leverages the Iroh P2P protocol to distribute LLM inference across decentralized, consumer-grade hardware without centralized coordination.",
        "Iroh provides robust, low-latency QUIC connections and NAT traversal, mitigating key networking bottlenecks in decentralized AI workloads.",
        "The architecture enables running large models by sharding layers and model weights across multiple peer nodes on a collaborative mesh."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/programming",
      "category": "engineering",
      "title": "Handsum: An LQIP Image File Format",
      "url": "https://nigeltao.github.io/blog/2026/handsum.html",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/gmzzeb",
      "score": 18,
      "comments": 1,
      "author": "carlana",
      "published": "2026-07-11T18:34:59Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Handsum introduces a custom Low-Quality Image Placeholder (LQIP) format to minimize page payload size and improve perceived loading speeds.",
        "Like BlurHash, it encodes visual previews into ultra-compact representations, reducing Cumulative Layout Shift (CLS) on modern web applications.",
        "Implementing LQIP formats allows developers to inline placeholder data directly within HTML/JSON payloads, eliminating extra HTTP requests for images."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/security",
      "category": "security",
      "title": "reaction: A daemon that scans program outputs for repeated patterns, and takes action",
      "url": "https://framagit.org/ppom/reaction",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/zzdc8x",
      "score": 22,
      "comments": 4,
      "author": "fanf",
      "published": "2026-07-12T01:15:49Z",
      "bullets": [
        "reaction is a modern, Go-based alternative to Fail2ban that scans log outputs and systemd journal for pattern-matching intrusion detection.",
        "SecOps can configure it to trigger immediate defensive actions, like nftables or iptables bans, upon detecting repeated failed login patterns.",
        "It provides a lightweight, dependency-free binary with lower resource consumption than Python-based tools for container and server hardening."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/devops",
      "category": "devops",
      "title": "Package Management as Org Chart",
      "url": "https://nesbitt.io/2026/07/10/package-management-as-org-chart.html",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/6fmohi",
      "score": 20,
      "comments": 3,
      "author": "calvin",
      "published": "2026-07-10T19:12:27Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Dependency graphs in package managers like npm or pip directly mirror an organization's communication structures and Conway's Law.",
        "Siloed teams managing internal registries like Artifactory create duplicate dependencies, increasing supply chain risks and maintenance overhead.",
        "Mapping software bill of materials (SBOMs) to org charts is critical for identifying package owners during active vulnerability remediation."
      ]
    },
